
==English==

===Noun===
'''Baronet'''  (''plural:'' '''[[Baronets]]''')

# A hereditary title, below a peerage and senior to most Knighthoods, entitling the bearer to the titular prefix "Sir" which is used in conjunction with the holder's christian name. It is inheritable by the eldest son and a few Baronetcies can also pass through the female line. A Baronetcy which is held by a Lady is called "Dame" {christian name} {surname}.

